1) Server: It's a place where we would be running our application.[we will get with killer koda]

2) Provisioning: When we are installing any software in top of operating system is known provisioning.

2.1)How to check java is installed or not?
ubuntu $ java --version

2.2)Before installing any software we should update our repository
    apt-get update
    apt install openjdk-17-jre-headless

"apt-get update" updates the local package index, fetching the latest package lists from the repositories specified in /etc/apt/sources.list or files in /etc/apt/sources.list.d/

